value.name: Carlos Menem - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Carlos Saúl Menem (Spanish pronunciation: [ˈkaɾlos 'me.nem] (); 2 July 1930 – 14 February 2021) was an Argentine lawyer and politician who served as the President of Argentina from 1989 to 1999. Ideologically, he identified as a Peronist and supported economically liberal policies. He led Argentina as president during the 1990s and implemented a free market liberalization.
